Title: Invisible Women: Data Bias in a World Designed for Men
Author: Caroline Criado Pérez
My Review: If you study/work in STEM, you probably shouldn't bother with this book. It is simply a 300-page list of facts, most of which I had already learned from working in tech. I was severely disappointed by the author's lack of analysis, which I was hoping-- and quite frankly expecting-- when I started the book. We have plenty of authors writing about these problems but there are not nearly enough who are proposing solutions. This author is no exception to that.
